		<p class="headingBlue"><b>What is capitalisation?</b></p>
		<p class="textP">Capitalisation is the writing of the first letter in a word in upper case and the remaining letters in lower case.</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>ngo was born on </i><b><i>E</i></b><i>aster </i><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>sland. </i><span class="s2"><b><i>H</i></b></span><i>e is fluent in </i><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>ascuense and </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>nglish.<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></i></p></li>
		<li><p class="p5"><i><b>H</b>is birthday is on 1 </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>pril – </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>ll </i><span class="s2"><b><i>F</i></b></span><i>ools’ </i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>ay!</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<br/>
		<p class="headingOrange"><b>What are the rules?</b></p>
		<p class="textNum"><span class="s3"><b>1)</b></span> Capitalisation is used<b><span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></b></p>
		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>a)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>at the beginning of a sentence</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>ngo was glad that he could visit Germany.</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>b)<span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span></b></span>in proper<b> </b>names<b> </b>of<b> </b>persons</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>ngo and </i><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>nga are friends. </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>iegfried, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>W</i></b></span><i>olfgang and </i><span class="s2"><b><i>O</i></b></span><i>skar are their new friends from Koblenz in Germany.</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p8"><span class="s3"><b>c)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in titles as parts of names of persons. Yet, when a title stands alone or follows the name, it is not capitalised.<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>rime </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>inister Gordon Brown and </i><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>hancellor Ingela Merkel gave a press conference. The </i><b><i>p</i></b><i>resident of the United States joined them. Ingela Merkel, the Pascuense </i><b><i>c</i></b><i>hancellor, was truly puzzled.</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>d)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of peoples<b> </b>(<i>Völker</i>)</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><i>the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>B</i></b></span><i>ritish, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>F</i></b></span><i>rench, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>reek, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>utch, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>panish, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>olish, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>anish<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></i></p></li>
		<li><p class="p5"><i>the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>ermans, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>mericans, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>talians, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>R</i></b></span><i>ussians, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>wedes</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>e)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of languages</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>erman, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>nglish, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>ascuense</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>f)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in trade names</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><i>Ingo loves his </i><span class="s2"><b><i>L</i></b></span><i>evi’s, but he sometimes forgets to check his pockets for </i><span class="s2"><b><i>K</i></b></span><i>leenex before the washing.<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>g)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of newspapers or magazines</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b><i>ingo</i><b><i>L</i></b><i>ingo </i><b><i>Q</i></b><i>uarterly</i></span>, <span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>he </i><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>uardian </i><span class="s2"><b><i>W</i></b></span><i>eekly, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>N</i></b></span><i>ew </i><span class="s2"><b><i>Y</i></b></span><i>ork </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>imes</i><b><i><span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></i></b></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>h)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of geographical features</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>ermany, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>R</i></b></span><i>hine </i><span class="s2"><b><i>V</i></b></span><i>alley, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>oselle, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>K</i></b></span><i>oblenz</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>i)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of monuments, bridges and buildings</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>F</i></b></span><i>ortress </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>hrenbreitstein, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>iffel </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>ower, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>B</i></b></span><i>erlin </i><span class="s2"><b><i>W</i></b></span><i>all</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>j)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of organizations, bands, companies, institutions or government agencies</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2">&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<b><i>A</i></b></span><i>mnesty </i><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>nternational, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>F</i></b></span><i>ury in the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>laughterhouse, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>icrosoft, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>K</i></b></span><i>oblenz </i><span class="s2"><b><i>U</i></b></span><i>niversity, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>US</i></b><i> </i><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>ongress, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>B</i></b></span><i>ritish </i><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>arliament</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>k)<span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span></b></span>in names of weekdays, months and holidays</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>F</i></b></span><i>riday, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>pril, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>ll </i><span class="s2"><b><i>F</i></b></span><i>ools’ </i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>ay, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>ingo</i><span class="s2"><b><i>L</i></b></span><i>ingo </i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>ay, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>N</i></b></span><i>ew </i><span class="s2"><b><i>Y</i></b></span><i>ear’s </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>ve<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>l)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names of historical documents, events, periods and movements</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>B</i></b></span><i>ritish </i><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>onstitution, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>occer </i><span class="s2"><b><i>W</i></b></span><i>orld</i><b><i> </i></b><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>up, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>ce </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>ge, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>hildren’s </i><span class="s2"><b><i>R</i></b></span><span class="s4"><i>i</i></span><i>ghts </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>ovement</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p8"><span class="s3"><b>m)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in names<b> </b>of religions and their members, in words denoting supreme beings, titles of holy books, holy events and festivities</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>hristianity, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>J</i></b></span><i>ews, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>uslims, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>H</i></b></span><i>indus, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>od, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>H</i></b></span><i>oly </i><span class="s2"><b><i>B</i></b></span><i>ible, the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>almud, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>hristmas, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>aster, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>hanksgiving</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p7"><span class="s3"><b>n)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in nouns, verbs and adjectives deriving from proper names</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>c</i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>onaldization, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>C</i></b></span><i>hristianisation, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>ingomania, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>A</i></b></span><i>mericanise, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>arxist, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>lizabethan, </i><span class="s2"><b>S</b></span>hakespearean</p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p8"><span class="s3"><b>o)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in the<b> </b>first<b> </b>and major words in titles of works of art (books, paintings, songs, plays, musicals, films; major = nouns, verbs, adjectives)</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>ractical </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>nglish </i><span class="s2"><b><i>U</i></b></span><i>sage, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>L</i></b></span><i>ord of the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>R</i></b></span><i>ings, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>ona </i><span class="s2"><b><i>L</i></b></span><i>isa, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>L</i></b></span><i>ucy in the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>ky with </i><span class="s2"><b><i>D</i></b></span><i>iamonds, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>W</i></b></span><i>aiting for </i><span class="s2"><b><i>G</i></b></span><i>odot, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>T</i></b></span><i>he </i><span class="s2"><b><i>P</i></b></span><i>hantom of the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>O</i></b></span><i>pera, </i><span class="s2"><b><i>W</i></b></span><i>hen </i><span class="s2"><b><i>H</i></b></span><i>arry </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>et </i><span class="s2"><b><i>S</i></b></span><i>ally</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p8"><span class="s3"><b>p)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in acronyms and abbreviations of proper names. They are written in full capitals.<span class="Apple-converted-space"> </span></p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><b><i>UNO</i></b><i>, </i><b><i>PC</i></b><i>, </i><b><i>NATO</i></b><i>, </i><b><i>UNESCO</i></b><i>, </i><b><i>JFK</i></b><i>, </i><b><i>NBA, ABBA</i></b></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="textNum"><span class="s3"><b>2)</b></span> Capitalisation is used under certain circumstances</p>
		<p class="p8"><span class="s3"><b>a)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>in directions and compass points<b> </b>(<i>Himmelsrichtungen</i>) when they refer to geographical regions that are also names.</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><i>Some of Ingo's friends come from the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>M</i></b></span><i>iddle </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>ast.</i></p>
		<p class="p5">Compare<i>: Some of Ingo's friends come from the east of Germany.</i></p></li>
</ul>

		<p class="p8"><span class="s3"><b>b)</b></span><span class="Apple-tab-span">	</span>for some Internet-related words.</p>

<ul>
		<li><p class="p5"><i>Ingo likes surfing the </i><span class="s2"><b><i>I</i></b></span><i>nternet and </i><span class="s2"><b><i>E</i></b></span><i>-</i><span class="s2"><b><i>L</i></b></span><i>earning. The </i><span class="s2"><b><i>WWW</i></b></span><i> has really helped.</i></p>
		<p class="p5">Compare: <i>TingoLingo has its own domain: visit www.tingolingo.de!</i></p></li>
</ul>

